==English==

====Etymology====
From {{Gr.}} ''para'' &#960;&#945;&#961;&#940; "besides" and φιλια ''[[-philia]]''  "love" or "friendship"

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}} 
{{en-noun-reg}} 

# A technical term for a [[sexual]] attraction of an unusual or [[pathological]] nature.
# Sexual arousal in response to sexual objects or situations which may interfere with the capacity for reciprocal affectionate sexual activity.
# Any of a group of sexual fantasies, urges and behaviors that are considered [[deviant]] with respect to cultural norms.

===Usage notes===
*It is important to notice that the term can be and is also used to imply "less mainstream sexual practices" but without necessarily negatively implying any dysfunction or 'wrongness'.

